This paper is primarily focused on the topic of differential privacy, which falls under the category of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security). The paper also utilizes compressive sensing, which is a technique related to information theory and signal processing, falling under the category of "cs.IT" (Information Theory). The compressive mechanism proposed in the paper involves constructing a compact synopsis, which can be seen as a form of data structure, falling under the category of "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with statistical queries and the release of statistical results, which are topics related to databases and machine learning, falling under the categories of "cs.DB" (Databases) and "cs.LG" (Machine Learning).
